    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Standalone TTS-only node. Voices the latest assistant text produced upstream on the current interaction (whatever node wrote it — Generate, CannedResponse, etc.), segments it into sentences, and synthesizes each on a dedicated TTS strand, emitting PCM frames via OnTtsAudio callbacks. Unlike GenerateAndSpeak it runs no LLM inference, so it can voice canned/scripted lines or any upstream-produced answer without paying for a generation pass. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
